'''Topical tobacco paste''' is a [[home remedy]] sometimes recommended as a treatment for [[wasp]], [[hornet]], [[fire ant]], [[scorpion]] or [[bee sting]]s,<ref>[http://pubs.caes.uga.edu/caespubs/pubcd/c782-w.html Beverly Sparks, "Stinging and Biting Pests of People"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070214061028/http://pubs.caes.uga.edu/caespubs/pubcd/c782-w.html |date=2007-02-14 }} Extension Entomologist of the University of Georgia College of Agricultural & Environmental Sciences Cooperative Extension Service.</ref>  though there is no scientific evidence that this home remedy works to relieve pain.<ref name="glaser">{{cite web | last =Glaser | first =David | title =Are wasp and bee stings alkali or acid and does neutralising their ph them give sting relief? | work = | publisher =www.insectstings.co.uk | date = | url =http://www.insectstings.co.uk/sting-acid-or-alkali.shtml | accessdate =2007-05-03 | deadurl =yes | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20070626073259/http://www.insectstings.co.uk/sting-acid-or-alkali.shtml | archivedate =2007-06-26 | df = }}</ref> For about 2 percent of people, allergic reactions can be life-threatening and require emergency treatment. 

